ECB Plans to Keep Bonds It Buys Until Maturity, Liikanen Says

-- B y   K a t i   P o h j a n p a l o
-- 
2011-10-14T09:40:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/ecb-plans-to-keep-bonds-it-buys-until-maturity-liikanen-says.html
 European Central Bank council
member  Erkki Liikanen  said the central bank intends to keep the
bonds it buys until maturity.  Liikanen, who also heads the Bank of Finland, spoke today
at a hearing in the Helsinki-based parliament. Bond purchases
made on the secondary market at market price are intended to
ensure the transmission of monetary policy, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kati Pohjanpalo at 
 kpohjanpalo@bloomberg.net  